This paper is about response generation in open domain dialogues, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach that enhances the sequence-to-sequence architecture with a goal tracking memory network, which involves machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the proposed model on two large-scale datasets, which involves large-scale data processing and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves modeling and managing the one-to-many relationship within open domain dialogues, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly studied in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
